<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-692432" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LMC-logo-1-289x300.jpg?resize=289%2C300&#038;ssl=1" alt="LMC, Nasarawa United" width="289" height="300" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LMC-logo-1-289x300.jpg?resize=289%2C300&amp;ssl=1 289w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LMC-logo-1-289x300.jpg?resize=56%2C58&amp;ssl=1 56w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LMC-logo-1-289x300.jpg?resize=187%2C194&amp;ssl=1 187w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/LMC-logo-1-289x300.jpg?resize=125%2C130&amp;ssl=1 125w" sizes="(max-width: 289px) 100vw, 289px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The League Management Company (LMC) has confirmed the report of the death of Chineme Martins, a defender with Nasarawa United FC, who slumped during the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) Matchday 23 against Katsina United in Lafia. The player was attended to by medics of the two clubs when he slumped and was later rushed to Dalhatu- Araf Specialist Hospital in Lafia where he was later pronounced dead. Chairman of LMC, Shehu Dikko said the league regrets the passing of the young man in his prime. “We commiserate with Nasarawa United and the immediate family of the late player”, Dikko said. The LMC expects that there would be a standard autopsy to establish the cause of the player’s death. “It is hoped that the findings of the autopsy would inform subsequent measures, if any that has not been addressed by the existing standard procedure”, the LMC stated. Furthermore, the LMC will keep engaging the club and the player’s immediate family to find the best way possible to offer support in this sad moment for the family and the Nigeria football family at large. npfl.ng Vanguard News A mid-season review of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) 2019/20 season was held on Tuesday, February 18, 2020, at the LMC head office in Abuja with far-reaching resolutions aimed at sustaining the progress that has been recorded and measures to be taken to prevent isolated cases of security breaches… February 19, 2020 In "Sports" The Board of National Nationwide League One (NLO), on Wednesday, applauded the League Management Company (LMC) for a successful organisation of just-concluded 2016/2017 Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) season. September 13, 2017 In "News" The League Management Company (LMC) has intervened by helping two out of three clubs indebted to ailing coach Kelechi Emeteole remit the amount which represented salary claims by the coach on the two clubs. March 13, 2017 In "Sports"